	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=6101&mid=108611728677515>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=6101&mid=108611728677515>Who should get</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=6101&mid=108611728677515#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Jun 1st 3:16 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=193711><span id= >technoeq</span></a><br><span id=notbold>80 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.92]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, I have to put my 2 cents in.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is an All/All belt, yes.  Most casters, if they play to benefit the guild as a whole, would pass on this and that shows character - so if you have casters rolling, you may want to ask why you are in a guild with those peeps who aren't looking at the bigger picture.  <br><br>I do have to say that no one should pass a dirty look off at a cleric that rolls on this tho.  I gave my hubbies cleric a spiked seahorse hide belt along with his warrior, not just because it has ok stats but because it has haste.  There are a lot of clerics out there that know how to heal and melee and at the higher lvl's clerics can be really nice dps.  Add a haste item to that with 15 WIS and you not only have a cleric with more mana (if they weren't already maxed wis before) AND a cleric with more dps.  Course, I'd love for my pally to have this over a warrior just because of the high WIS but it's all a matter of preference, and everyone will put in their opinion and is entitled.  I did. =)</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
